{0 'ABM Gold Corp will use the proceeds ofan initial public offering of seven mln shares of stock at 10dlrs a share to increase its interest in three Canadiancompanies, said co-managing underwriters PaineWebber Inc andAdvest Inc. ABM Gold manages and develops properties of Sonora GoldCorp <SON.TO>, Goldenbell Resources Inc <GBL.TO>, United GoldCorp <UGC.V> and Inca Resources Inc <IRI.TO>. Proceeds will be used to raise its stake in Sonora, buy a15 pct interest in the net profits of Sonora\'s Jamestown mine,and buy capital stock of Goldenball and United, they said. ABM Gold explores, acquires and develops gold properties inCalifornia, and also processes gold-bearing ore into goldbullion. The co-managing underwriters said they are selling 3.5 mlnshares in the U.S. and Canada, while an interational offeringwill be managed by PaineWebber International. The underwritershave been granted an option to buy up to an additional 105,000shares to cover over-allotments. Reuter',1 ACQ}
