{0 'The U.S. Secretary of CommerceMalcolm Baldrige said a further decline of the dollar would notbe productive. He told reporters here that Treasury Secretary James Baker\"feels, and I feel the same way, that a further dollar fallwould be counterproductive.\" Baldrige also said governments cannot determine long-termcurrency exchange rates and that currencies would eventuallyreflect underlying economic fundamentals. The U.S. Commerce Secretary is in Hong Kong after stops inPeking and Seoul on an Asian trade tour. REUTER',1 MONEY-FX}
