{0 'China\'s total wage bill for stateemployees grew too fast in the first quarter, because ofexcessive bonuses, allowances and overtime pay, the officialEconomic Information newspaper said. It said the total wage bill in the period was 38.7 billionyuan, an increase of 16.7 pct over the first quarter of 1986,when the bill grew a year-on-year 16.3 pct. The increaseaccounted for 39.6 pct of planned wage rises in all of 1987. It said bonus payments rose a 42.6 pct, far in excess ofgrowth in productivity. Industrial output grew a 14.1 pct inthe period. The newspaper said state allowances rose in the period by20 pct over the corresponding 1986 quarter, with some areas andwork units increasing coal and electricity allowances on theirown without proper authorisation. It said overtime pay rose a year-on-year 32 pct, with someenterprises ignoring official regulations in their payments. REUTER',1 INCOME}
